Summary: Great Lakes Dredge & Dock Corporation is the largest provider of dredging, land reclamation and beach nourishment services in the United States, and the only U.S. dredging company with significant international operations. With the largest and most diverse dredging fleet in the US, Great Lakes serves a wide range of customers including the US Army Corps of Engineers; state, local and foreign governments; and private companies both international and domestic. Headquartered in Houston, Texas, GLDD has more than 200 pieces of dredging plant located strategically throughout North America and in various locations throughout the world. We are currently seeking an Offshore Wind Technology Manager to join our team. 
The utility scale Offshore Wind market in the US is expanding rapidly, to meet commitments from the States for renewable energy generation and carbon free energy solutions for the next decade and beyond. The Offshore Wind Technology Manager is responsible for technology planning, development and application for the US offshore wind market, for both fixed and floating developments. This role also includes the technology oversight of new build vessel(s) related to offshore wind, such as the GLDD Subsea Rock Installation Vessel, currently in the design phase and moving into construction later this year. This is a key position to support GLDDâ€™s strategic entry into the burgeoning US offshore wind market and capture a tremendous growth opportunity as the world transitions to cleaner, carbon free sources of energy. The position reports directly to the GLDD Senior VP, Offshore Wind. 
Duties and Responsibilities: 
Duties and responsibilities of the position include: 
Building up GLDDâ€™s capability in technology development relating to Offshore Wind, for both fixed and floating applications. Participating in industry forums and partnerships for the development of offshore wind technologies and applications for the US market. Evaluating emerging technologies for offshore wind both in the US and internationally. 
Collaborating with industry and academia for the development of US based offshore wind supply base technologies and capabilities. Leading GLDD participation in R&D public funding rounds for offshore wind. 
Developing cost effective, innovative solutions for the upcoming offshore wind farm bids in the US Northeast and mid-Atlantic States to ensure GLDDâ€™s competitive edge. Participating in the bidding process in a technology advisory role. 
Provide expertise in metocean data analysis and vessel operability windows as the SME in Naval Architecture and Marine Engineering technologies. 
Provide technical oversight for offshore wind vessel engineering and build(s). Champion technologies relating to low/zero carbon emissions, digital simulations, autonomous operations, artificial intelligence. 
Qualifications: 
Professional qualifications for this important position include: 
M.S. or PhD in Naval Architecture & Marine Engineering or related field; 
15+ years of experience in technology development (offshore oil and gas or offshore wind); 
Experience in offshore wind technologies is a definite plus; 
Experience participating in industry-wide technology forums; 
Experience in shipbuilding industry. 
